Illovo Raises $134 Million to Fund Swaziland Sugar Business, Power Plant

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-05-16T10:56:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/illovo-raises-134-million-to-fund-swaziland-sugar-business-power-plant.html
Illovo Sugar Ltd. (ILV)  said it borrowed
940 million emalangeni ($134 million) to fund the expansion of a
sugar factory and power plant at its Ubombo Sugar Ltd. unit in
Swaziland.  The eight-year loan was sourced from commercial banks in
Swaziland and was arranged by Investec Ltd.,  Nedbank Group Ltd. (NED) 
and Standard Bank Group Ltd, Mt. Edgecombe, South Africa-based
Illovo said in an e-mailed statement today.  Ubombo is 60 percent owned by Illovo and 40 percent held by
a trust on behalf of the Swazi nation.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  